      -- We need to show that for any `i`, `i` is less than or equal to the supremum of the set `{ s | s ∈ range (fun i ↦ (M_ i).toSubmodule) }`.
      -- Given that `M_` is filter-complete, we know that for any `i`, `M_ i` is less than or equal to the supremum of `M_ j` for `j` in the range.
      -- We can leverage this fact to show the required inequality for the submodules.
